# Cursor Rules for Card Battle Client

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 15 project using:
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- TanStack Query (React Query)
- Zustand for state management
- React Hook Form with Zod validation

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Use functional components with hooks
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions
- Use path aliases (@/*) for imports from src directory
- Prefer named exports over default exports when possible

## File Structure
- Components in `src/components/`
- Pages/routes in `src/app/`
- Hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Services/API calls in `src/services/`
- State management in `src/store/`
- Types in `type.d.ts` at root

## Import Conventions
- Use `@/` prefix for imports from src directory
- Group imports: external packages, then internal modules
- Use absolute imports with path aliases

## TypeScript
- Enable strict mode (already configured)
- Use proper types for all props and functions
- Define shared types in `type.d.ts`
